<p class="instruction">Alternative forms of the “Glory be” and “Praise the Lord” are found in <a href="#add_dir">Additional Directions.</a></p>
<p class="instruction">The following or some other suitable hymn or Psalm may be sung or said.</p>
<h3>Phos hilaron <em>O Gladsome Light</em></h3>
<div class="poetic">
    <p class="line">O gladsome light,</p>
    <p class="line">pure brightness of the ever-living Father in heaven,</p>
    <p class="indented_line">O Jesus Christ, holy and blessed!</p>
    <p class="line">Now as we come to the setting of the sun,</p>
    <p class="line">and our eyes behold the vesper light,</p>
    <p class="indented_line">we sing your praises, O God: Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.</p>
    <p class="line">You are worthy at all times to be praised by happy voices,</p>
    <p class="indented_line">O Son of God, O Giver of Life,</p>
    <p class="indented_line">and to be glorified through all the worlds.</p>
</div>
<p class="instruction">Then follows</p>

