<a name="add_dir"></a>
<h3>Additional Directions: Morning and Evening Prayer</h3>
<p class="instruction">The Confession and Apostles’ Creed may be omitted, provided each is said at least once during the course of the day.</p>
<p class="instruction">The Gloria Patri in the opening versicles may be said in unison. The following form of the Gloria Patri may alternately be used:</p>
<div class="poetic">
    <p class="line">Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:</p>
    <p class="indented_line">As it was in the beginning, is now, and will be forever. Amen.</p>
</div>
<p class="instruction">The Officiant and People may join in saying “Alleluia” (except in Lent) as an alternative to the versicles “Praise the Lord. The Lord’s name be praised.”</p>
<p class="instruction">If an offering is to be received, it is appropriate to do so during the hymn or anthem following the collects.</p>
<p class="instruction">A sermon may be preached after the lessons, after the hymn or anthem following the collects, or after the conclusion of the Office.</p>